


 🔰 Week 1 – REST API with Spring Boot (No Database)

Goal: Learn annotations, build routes, understand request/response, complete a mini project.



 🗓️ Day 1 — Spring Boot Setup + GET/POST Basics  
⏱ Time: 4 hours  
- 1 hr: Spring Boot setup using Spring Initializr + run your first app  
- 1 hr: Create a `@RestController` + basic `@GetMapping`, `@PostMapping`  
- 1 hr: Understand how JSON works in requests/responses  
- 1 hr: Test with Postman, play around with returning lists & strings  



 🗓️ Day 2 — Route Parameters & JSON Input  
⏱ Time: 4–5 hours  
- 1 hr: Learn `@PathVariable` and `@RequestParam`  
- 1.5 hrs: Practice sending/receiving JSON via `@RequestBody`  
- 1 hr: Store data in a List, simulate database  
- 1 hr: Practice POST + GET combo to save and retrieve tasks  



 🗓️ Day 3 — Full CRUD with In-Memory Data  
⏱ Time: 5 hours  
- 1 hr: Add `@PutMapping` to update objects  
- 1 hr: Add `@DeleteMapping` and test deletion logic  
- 1.5 hrs: Error handling and return meaningful messages  
- 1.5 hrs: Review all routes in Postman, polish code  



 🗓️ Day 4 — Mini Project: ToDo / Notes API  
⏱ Time: 5–6 hours  
- 1 hr: Plan your API endpoints and data structure  
- 3 hrs: Build the entire REST API with full CRUD  
- 1 hr: Test everything thoroughly  
- 1 hr: Clean code, use comments, organize project  

✅ End of Week 1: You know how to build and test REST APIs confidently using annotations only.

===================================================================================================


 🔧 Week 2 – Spring Data JPA + H2/PostgreSQL Integration

Goal: Learn entity mapping, repositories, and move from in-memory to real DB.



 🗓️ Day 5 — JPA Fundamentals + Entity Creation  
⏱ Time: 4 hours  
- 1 hr: Understand what JPA is and how it works  
- 1.5 hrs: Create an entity class with `@Entity`, `@Id`, etc.  
- 1.5 hrs: Learn and implement Spring Data `JpaRepository`  



 🗓️ Day 6 — H2 Database Integration  
⏱ Time: 4–5 hours  
- 1 hr: Configure H2 database and set up `application.properties`  
- 1 hr: Replace in-memory storage with H2 database  
- 1.5 hrs: Test all CRUD operations again with database  
- 1 hr: View data using H2 web console  



 🗓️ Day 7 — Move to PostgreSQL  
⏱ Time: 5 hours  
- 1.5 hrs: Install PostgreSQL and pgAdmin  
- 1 hr: Configure Spring Boot to use PostgreSQL  
- 1 hr: Update project to use PostgreSQL instead of H2  
- 1.5 hrs: Run and test all CRUD routes with PostgreSQL  



 🗓️ Day 8 — Final Project + Cleanup  
⏱ Time: 5–6 hours  
- 3 hrs: Finalize your mini-project with Spring Boot + PostgreSQL  
- 1 hr: Add project structure (DTO, Service, Controller layers)  
- 1 hr: Test thoroughly in Postman  
- 1 hr: Clean up files, add README (optional)  

✅ End of Week 2: You’re capable of building full-stack backend APIs using real database persistence.


---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

 ⚡️ After Week 2 — Java 8+ Features (Optional but recommended)

Once you're done, you can spend 1 more week (1–2 hours/day) learning:
- Lambdas
- Streams
- Optionals
- Method references

